    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1043"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1043">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 125.8273/57.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Departments May 19 received. General Antonio Villareal who is Governor of this
                    State and commander of the Constitutionalist forces assures me that a white flag
                    of truce will be respected by Constitutionalists at any time which comes out of
                    Saltillo bringing Vice Consul Silliman and party of Americans. If Vice Consul
                    Silliman is in party an escort also under flag of truce will start immediately
                    to <pb facs="0781" n="665" xml:id="pg_665"/> meet party from Federal lines and
                    Consul Silliman will be escorted by Constitutionalist forces to Monterey with
                    every facility available. General Villareal will also order a military
                    automobile to be in readiness to bring Vice Consul Silliman to Monterey.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
